有拘捕令吗 有没有犯罪记录
-Any warrants?
-Record's clean.

57
00:11:31,940 --> 00:11:35,280
算了吧 这么难找的人
一定能找到理由通缉他
Come on! A guy this hard to find?
Gotta be wanted for something.

58
00:11:35,570 --> 00:11:36,910
他没有任何犯罪记录
His record is clean.

59
00:11:37,780 --> 00:11:38,950
那么
So,

60
00:11:42,910 --> 00:11:44,580
怎么才能找到这个雷彻
how do we find this Reacher?

61
00:11:44,910 --> 00:11:48,160
你无法找到 除非他想让你找到他
Obviously, you don't find this guy
unless he wants to be found.

62
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:53,580
打扫一下长官
有个叫杰克-雷彻的人想见你
Excuse me, sir. There's
a Jack Reacher here to see you.

63
00:12:01,930 --> 00:12:03,140
你有什么事吗
Can l help you?

64
00:12:03,760 --> 00:12:05,640
詹姆斯-巴尔
James Barr.

65
00:12:12,980 --> 00:12:15,780
好了 你见过他了 你们怎么认识的
So, now you've seen him.
How do you know him?

66
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:18,320
为什么不对他实行保护性监禁
Why wasn't he in protective custody?

67
00:12:19,940 --> 00:12:21,570
是工作疏忽
That was an oversight.

68
00:12:21,650 --> 00:12:24,000
是监狱里的势利小人把他扔进了狼窝
More like some Corrections flunky
threw him to the wolves.

69
00:12:24,700 --> 00:12:25,950
好像是这样
Just as likely.

70
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:28,120
可是事到如今已经无法挽回
But it's done and we can't undo it.

71
00:12:28,330 --> 00:12:29,370
现在怎么样了
So what happens now?

72
00:12:29,620 --> 00:12:31,790
好吧 现在他处在昏迷中
Well, now he's in a coma.

73
00:12:32,620 --> 00:12:35,630
他昏迷不醒
We'll try him when he wakes up.
lf he wakes up.

74
00:12:35,960 --> 00:12:37,380
如果他能醒过来 我们要审判他
好了该你谈谈了 雷彻
Okay? Now it's your turn, Reacher.

75
00:12:37,790 --> 00:12:39,800
他为什么要你做证人
Why did he call you as a witness?

76
00:12:40,130 --> 00:12:41,470
我不相信他会这么做
l don't believe he did.

77
00:12:41,670 --> 00:12:43,270
他指名道姓要你来
Well, l believe
he asked for you by name.

78
00:12:44,340 --> 00:12:45,900
我能看一下证据吗
Any chance l could look
at the evidence?

79
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:47,600
你回答完几个问题再说
No way.
Not till you answer some questions.

80
00:12:47,680 --> 00:12:48,930
很高兴认识你
Nice meeting you.

81
00:12:49,010 --> 00:12:50,360
嗨 嗨 嗨!
站住 雷彻先生
-Hey. Hey. Hey!
-Mr Reacher.

82
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:51,980
- 嘿 别动
- 嗨，站在原地别动
-Mr Reacher!
-Hey, stop! Stop right there!

83
00:12:52,060 --> 00:12:53,440
我们有有言在先
We had a deal.

84
00:12:53,520 --> 00:12:55,770
我带你去见巴尔 你告诉我你了解的情况
l take you to Barr,
you tell me what you know.

85
00:12:55,850 --> 00:12:58,610
你说他射杀了五个人 可是他昏迷不醒
l know you say he shot five people,
l know he's in a coma.

86
00:12:58,690 --> 00:12:59,820
有个公交车站
l know there's a bus station
three miles away

87
00:12:59,980 --> 00:13:01,740
我用24分钟走到那
and l can walk there in 24 minutes.

88
00:13:01,860 --> 00:13:03,200
你要放弃你的朋友
So you're just going to
walk out on your friend?

89
00:13:03,700 --> 00:13:05,950
- 他不是我的朋友
- 那他为什么会要求你来
-He's not my friend.
-Why'd he ask for you,then?

90
00:13:06,030 --> 00:13:09,030
跟他杀死五个人是一个原因
Well, same reason he shot five people,
he's crazy.

91
00:13:09,160 --> 00:13:10,210
他疯了 等一下
Hey. Hold on.

92
00:13:10,490 --> 00:13:11,540
别拦着我
Don't do that.

93
00:13:11,700 --> 00:13:13,330
你们俩这么做卑鄙了
Well, this is a new low,
even for both of you.

94
00:13:14,710 --> 00:13:16,300
没有我在场 你们不能和我的委托人谈话
You do not talk to my client
without me present.

95
00:13:16,370 --> 00:13:17,420
你知道
You know that.

96
00:13:17,540 --> 00:13:20,670
我们没有和他谈话 他处在昏迷之中
We weren't talking to your client.
He's in a coma, for Christ's sakes.

97
00:13:20,750 --> 00:13:23,260
- 你是巴尔的律师
- 海伦-罗丁 杰克-雷彻
-You're Barr's attorney?
-Helen Rodin, Jack Reacher.

98
00:13:23,420 --> 00:13:25,180
- 杰克-雷彻?
- 海伦罗丁
-Jack Reacher?
-Helen Rodin.

99
00:13:25,340 --> 00:13:26,890
是的 她是地方检察官的女儿
Yeah, she's the
District Attorney's daughter.

100
00:13:27,010 --> 00:13:28,010
这事儿说来话长
lt's a good story, actually.

101
00:13:28,090 --> 00:13:29,220
这事儿说来话长
l'd like to hear it.

102
00:13:29,430 --> 00:13:31,430
你们是怎么找到他的
How'd you find him?
How'd they find you?

103
00:13:31,560 --> 00:13:34,060
你不能和这个人谈话
You can't be talking to this man.
Two strikes in one day.

104
00:13:34,180 --> 00:13:36,020
不是你想像的那样 是他找到的我们
-lt's not what it looks like.
-He came to us.

105
00:13:36,520 --> 00:13:38,770
- 你见了检察官
- 这样做违法吗
-You went to the D.A.?
-ls there a law against that?

106
00:13:38,940 --> 00:13:40,280
目前你还没有违法
None you're currently breaking.

107
00:13:40,520 --> 00:13:42,450
行啦 别把大家搞得下不来台
Come on, before this gets awkward.
Now, hey.

108
00:13:42,570 --> 00:13:44,870
快说 法庭上见
Say, "See you in court." For me.

109
00:13:45,110 --> 00:13:46,530
再见侦探
Goodbye, Detective.

110
00:13:46,860 --> 00:13:48,540
- 很高兴认识你
- 我也是
-Weird meeting you.
-Likewise.

111
00:13:48,870 --> 00:13:49,960
走吧
Let's go.

112
00:13:52,749 --> 00:13:54,083
So...

113
00:13:57,210 --> 00:13:58,550
你是杰克-雷彻
你是检察官的女儿
So, you're Jack Reacher.

114
00:13:58,880 --> 00:14:01,380
走吧
-So you're the D.A.'s daughter.
-Oh, Jesus. Please.

115
00:14:01,460 --> 00:14:03,300
－上帝 这种工作关系合法吗
－幸运的是合法
-ls that even legal?
-Fortunately.

116
00:14:03,550 --> 00:14:05,790
－怎么会有这种安排
－你宣誓作证之后再告诉你
-How does that happen?
-l'll tell you after deposition.

117
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:06,920
别让我宣誓作证
You don't want to depose me.

118
00:14:06,970 --> 00:14:08,090
你是被告证人
Oh, well, you're my only
defence witness.

119
00:14:08,220 --> 00:14:10,890
- 我不是
- 你的朋友詹姆斯认为你是
-l'm not a defence witness.
-Your friend James thinks you are.

120
00:14:10,970 --> 00:14:12,470
为什么所有人都认为他是我朋友
He's not my friend.
Why does everyone assume that?

121
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:13,600
为什么所有人都认为他是我的朋友
Well, why else would he ask for you

122
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:14,720
他要求见你 你来帮助他
and why would you
come here to help him?

123
00:14:14,810 --> 00:14:18,230
我不是来帮助他 是为了把他埋了
l didn't come here to help him.
l came here to bury him.

124
00:14:39,620 --> 00:14:41,420
(布鲁希尔建筑公司)

125
00:14:43,630 --> 00:14:44,850
林斯基
Linsky.

126
00:14:47,170 --> 00:14:48,800
杰克-雷彻是什么人
Who the hell is Jack Reacher?

127
00:14:50,640 --> 00:14:53,280
-你为什么这么难找
- 不可能找到我的
-So why are you so hard to find?
-l'm impossible to find.

128
00:14:53,350 --> 00:14:54,470
为什么找不到
Why is that?

129
00:14:54,810 --> 00:14:57,980
这么说吧 这是我的职业习惯
Well, you could say it started out as an
exercise and became an addiction.

130
00:14:58,640 --> 00:15:00,150
你逃跑吗
Are you on the run?

131
00:15:02,520 --> 00:15:04,700
我的车要开了 快点吧 律师
My bus is leaving.
You better hurry, counsellor.

132
00:15:04,820 --> 00:15:05,900
你是怎么认识巴尔的
How do you know James Barr?

133
00:15:05,980 --> 00:15:07,610
-你为什么要替他辩护  
-我是律师
-Why are you representing him?
-l'm a lawyer.

134
00:15:07,690 --> 00:15:10,330
公共辩护人也有机会证明他无罪
So is a public defender, with just as
much chance of clearing Barr.

135
00:15:10,490 --> 00:15:11,790
我并不是想证明他无罪
l'm not trying to clear him,

136
00:15:11,860 --> 00:15:14,330
而是要他不被判死刑
l am just trying
to keep him off death row.

137
00:15:15,030 --> 00:15:17,880
-你想证明他精神失常
-这也是一种选择
-By proving he's insane?
-Well, that's one option.

138
00:15:18,120 --> 00:15:19,620
跟你爸爸做对
And sticking it to your father because...

139
00:15:19,710 --> 00:15:22,170
不是他 是地方检察官办公室
No. Not my father.
The Office of the District Attorney.

140
00:15:22,290 --> 00:15:24,970
因为地方检察官办公室从未承认你是淑女
Because the Office of the District
Attorney never bought you a pony.

141
00:15:25,960 --> 00:15:28,720
罗丁检察官从未打输过死刑的案件
知道为什么吗
D.A. Rodin's never lost a capital case.
You know why?

142
00:15:28,880 --> 00:15:30,350
政客都爱仗势欺人
lmpeccable tailoring.

143
00:15:30,470 --> 00:15:33,310
-他从来都不接打不赢的案子
-知己知彼
-He never picks a fight he can'twin.
-Worked for the Red Baron.

144
00:15:33,390 --> 00:15:35,060
每个谋杀嫌疑犯都有两个选择
Every murder suspect in this town
is given a choice.

145
00:15:35,180 --> 00:15:36,810
认罪或者面对死刑
Confess or face death.

146
00:15:36,970 --> 00:15:39,230
和从未输过的检察官打官司
Against a D.A. who never loses.

147
00:15:39,480 --> 00:15:41,480
我的律师事务所相信无罪的人
My firm has reason to believe
more than one innocent man

148
00:15:41,560 --> 00:15:43,060
但都会毫不抵抗就认罪伏法
has gone down without a fight.

149
00:15:43,650 --> 00:15:45,150
我明白了
Oh, l get it.

150
00:15:46,230 --> 00:15:47,320
你是个理想主义者
You're an idealist.

151
00:15:47,820 --> 00:15:49,660
不 我是和平主义者
No. l'm a pacifist.

152
00:15:49,900 --> 00:15:51,250
想废除死刑是高尚行为
lt's a noble crusade.

153
00:15:51,490 --> 00:15:55,240
但这次你打不赢 相信我
詹姆斯-巴尔有罪
But this is not the fight. Trust me.
James Barr's guilty.

154
00:15:55,410 --> 00:15:57,210
你还没看证据呢
You haven't even seen the evidence.

155
00:16:01,540 --> 00:16:03,260
这是保密谈话吗
ls this a privileged conversation?

156
00:16:03,370 --> 00:16:07,100
对 是对诉讼委托人的谈话
你说的每一句话都不能转述
Of course, it's a client conference.
Nothing you say here can be repeated.

157
00:16:09,260 --> 00:16:11,850
有四种人会参军
There are four types of people
who join the military.

158
00:16:11,920 --> 00:16:13,720
有人是为了家族荣誉
For some, it's a family trade.

159
00:16:14,220 --> 00:16:16,560
有爱国者渴望为国效劳
Others are patriots, eager to serve.

160
00:16:16,890 --> 00:16:18,890
还有些为了工作
Next, you have those
who just need a job.

