Hey, Gunny, you mind if l ask you
kind of a personal question?

1266
01:44:40,690 --> 01:44:42,530
你认为我不会再射击吗
What, you don't think
l can shoot any more?

1267
01:44:43,230 --> 01:44:44,860
好枪法很难保持一辈子
lt is a perishable skill.

1268
01:44:45,730 --> 01:44:47,080
是啊
Yeah, well,

1269
01:44:47,650 --> 01:44:49,750
太阳一小时后就升起来了
the sun will be up in an hour.

1270
01:44:51,240 --> 01:44:52,580
我们走
Let's get going.

1271
01:45:09,590 --> 01:45:11,760
我听到他们叫你翟科
l heard them call you the Zec.

1272
01:45:12,550 --> 01:45:13,890
那是囚犯的意思 是吗
That means "prisoner."

1273
01:45:15,760 --> 01:45:16,940
是的
Yes?

1274
01:45:19,850 --> 01:45:21,270
告诉我 杀了这么多人
Tell me, killing all those people,

1275
01:45:22,020 --> 01:45:23,520
我相信你赚的钱
l have to believe the money
you're making

1276
01:45:23,600 --> 01:45:25,030
不可能足够用来
can't possibly be enough to just...

1277
01:45:25,110 --> 01:45:26,360
说够了吗
Enough?

1278
01:45:26,610 --> 01:45:28,450
根本没有这回事
There is no such thing.

1279
01:45:28,780 --> 01:45:30,780
我们只拿属于我们的东西
We take what can be taken.

1280
01:45:31,110 --> 01:45:32,660
我们就是这么做的
This is what we do.

1281
01:45:35,120 --> 01:45:36,460
而你呢
And you?

1282
01:45:38,120 --> 01:45:40,710
他我能理解 可是你呢
This one l think l understand, but you?

1283
01:45:41,370 --> 01:45:42,460
你是为什么
Why'd you do it?

1284
01:45:42,790 --> 01:45:45,130
我没得选择
You make it sound like l had a choice.

1285
01:45:45,290 --> 01:45:46,460
你没有吗
Oh, didn't you?

1286
01:45:49,960 --> 01:45:51,310
你会懂的
You'll see.

1287
01:45:55,140 --> 01:45:58,480
你们应该知道 我们已经采取了措施
You should know l've taken steps,
that if anything happens...

1288
01:45:58,560 --> 01:46:02,280
如果你发生意外
也会在你父亲面前
lf anything happens to you,
it will happen in front of your father

1289
01:46:02,390 --> 01:46:04,440
他祈求留你一条小命
while he begs for your life.

1290
01:46:06,650 --> 01:46:08,990
现在你必须说服他忘掉这一切
You should never have involved him.

1291
01:46:09,320 --> 01:46:13,040
为了你
Now you will have to convince him
to forget,for your sake

1292
01:46:13,110 --> 01:46:15,370
也为了他
and for his.

1293
01:46:16,240 --> 01:46:19,920
你不说话 我能看到你眼中充满了蔑视
You say nothing,
but l see defiance in your eyes.

1294
01:46:20,660 --> 01:46:23,510
这种眼神我见多了
That is a look l have seen
many, many times.

1295
01:46:23,830 --> 01:46:26,180
等那个大兵来了之后
When the soldier comes,

1296
01:46:26,250 --> 01:46:28,670
你亲眼看着他死去
那会改变你的想法
when you watch how he dies,
it will change you.

1297
01:46:29,170 --> 01:46:31,390
到时你就会想忘记我了
You will want to forget me then.

1298
01:46:42,180 --> 01:46:43,430
雷彻
Reacher?

1299
01:46:43,520 --> 01:46:44,860
你好吗
Are you okay?

1300
01:46:45,100 --> 01:46:46,320
他们要杀你
They're ready for you.

1301
01:46:47,270 --> 01:46:48,900
他们这么认为
They'd like to think so.

1302
01:46:49,860 --> 01:46:52,360
别来 不要为了我
Don't do this.
Please don't do this. Not for me.

1303
01:46:52,440 --> 01:46:54,070
海伦, 他们不会伤害你的
Listen, Helen, they're not gonna

1304
01:46:54,190 --> 01:46:58,170
在没有抓到我之前
hurt you until they have me.
And that's never going to happen.

1305
01:46:58,370 --> 01:46:59,540
你听我说
You hear me?

1306
01:47:00,620 --> 01:47:01,710
你要坚持住
You just hang in there.

1307
01:47:03,540 --> 01:47:05,380
我会去救你
'Cause l'm coming to get you.

1308
01:47:07,120 --> 01:47:08,470
快说你相信我
Now say you believe me.

1309
01:47:09,960 --> 01:47:11,340
我相信你
l believe you.

1310
01:47:43,160 --> 01:47:45,040
这是个馊主意
This was a bad idea.

1311
01:48:03,930 --> 01:48:05,560
老年仔 准备射击
Any time now, Gunny.

1312
01:48:20,610 --> 01:48:22,210
该死
Shit.

1313
01:48:33,880 --> 01:48:35,420
你在哪里 老牛仔
Where the hell are you, Gunny?

1314
01:52:53,720 --> 01:52:55,390
臭手
Suck it!

1315
01:53:06,570 --> 01:53:08,070
你该走了
You should go.

1316
01:53:51,283 --> 01:53:52,617
Toss it.

1317
01:56:51,040 --> 01:56:53,140
我知道你是在那里 爱默生
l know you're in there, Emerson.

1318
01:56:56,960 --> 01:56:59,640
我有你的犯罪证据
lt was staring me right in the face.

1319
01:57:01,300 --> 01:57:04,810
一个证据不能解释一切
The one piece that just didn't fit.

1320
01:57:05,640 --> 01:57:07,110
硬币
The quarter.

1321
01:57:09,480 --> 01:57:12,450
没人想到计时表的硬币就是证据
Nobody would have thought
to dump that meter.

1322
01:57:14,150 --> 01:57:15,650
连我都不会这么想
Not even me.

1323
01:57:59,150 --> 01:58:01,150
你错怪了我的父亲
You were wrong about my father.

1324
01:58:03,150 --> 01:58:05,280
我不会扩大事态
l wouldn't make a big thing of it.

1325
01:58:22,630 --> 01:58:23,850
他是谁
Who is he?

1326
01:58:23,970 --> 01:58:25,510
他是二号人物
That's John Doe Number Two.

1327
01:58:25,680 --> 01:58:28,850
暗杀行动的策划者
The man on the grassy knoll.
The thing under the bed.

1328
01:58:30,020 --> 01:58:31,690
他们叫他翟科
They call him the Zec.

1329
01:58:31,980 --> 01:58:34,190
翟科 就是囚犯
Zec? Prisoner.

1330
01:58:35,310 --> 01:58:36,690
你的真正名字是什么
What's your real name?

1331
01:58:39,860 --> 01:58:41,610
我是十月出生的
l was born in October.

1332
01:58:41,690 --> 01:58:44,040
当我数到我生日的那月 我就开枪
When l get to my birthday,
l'm gonna pull the trigger.

1333
01:58:44,360 --> 01:58:46,290
一  二
One. Two.

1334
01:58:46,360 --> 01:58:49,990
切诺维克
Chelovek. Zec Chelovek.

1335
01:58:51,700 --> 01:58:53,210
切诺维克 翟科-切诺维克
Chelovek?

1336
01:58:53,870 --> 01:58:55,370
切诺维克是人名
Chelovek? Human.

1337
01:58:57,380 --> 01:58:58,920
你叫囚犯人
Prisoner Human Being.

1338
01:59:00,050 --> 01:59:03,390
- 那是你的真名吗
- 我就记得这些
-That's your real name?
-That is all l remember.

1339
01:59:06,550 --> 01:59:08,020
打电话给警察
Call the police.

1340
01:59:11,560 --> 01:59:13,350
你刚才真想杀了他吗
Were you really going to shoot him?

1341
01:59:15,060 --> 01:59:16,900
不会的
l knew l wouldn't have to.

1342
01:59:18,020 --> 01:59:21,900
看一眼就知道会是想活的人
One look at this guy and you know
he'll do anything to survive.

1343
01:59:22,230 --> 01:59:24,410
你看一眼就知道我不是吹牛的人
One look at me
and you know l'm not bluffing.

1344
01:59:24,690 --> 01:59:27,200
我有件急事
Yes, l have an emergency at...

1345
01:59:28,070 --> 01:59:29,370
好 我等着
Yes, l'll hold.

1346
01:59:33,080 --> 01:59:34,420
我们不着急
We're in no hurry.

1347
01:59:37,040 --> 01:59:39,260
你住监狱 就像在家里一样舒服
With a name like yours,
you're gonna feel right at home.

1348
01:59:39,580 --> 01:59:42,260
监狱 在美国
Prison? ln America?

1349
01:59:42,750 --> 01:59:46,930
能去美国监狱 就像住进养老院
A retirement home.
lf l go to prison at all.

1350
01:59:47,050 --> 01:59:48,220
你认为能逃脱罪名吗
You think you're gonna walk?

1351
01:59:48,430 --> 01:59:51,100
你是个无家可归的人 被通缉的杀人犯
You are a homeless drifter
wanted for murder.

1352
01:59:51,430 --> 01:59:55,780
我是在错误时间来这里的老头
Meanwhile, l am an old man
in the wrong place at the wrong time.

1353
01:59:56,100 --> 02:00:00,200
多亏了你
Thanks to you,
who is left to say othewise? Who?

1354
02:00:00,270 --> 02:00:04,120
谁呢
对 我有一件急事
Yes, hello? Yes, there's...
l have an emergency.

1355
02:00:04,230 --> 02:00:06,280
我们走着瞧 看谁进监狱
We'll see which one of us
goes to prison.

1356
02:00:06,440 --> 02:00:08,950
也许有三四个人死
There are maybe
three, four people dead.

1357
02:00:10,490 --> 02:00:11,960
- 好
- 我的打赌
-Okay.
-My bet?

1358
02:00:13,620 --> 02:00:15,000
没人
Neither one.

1359
02:00:18,120 --> 02:00:19,670
你做了什么
What did you do?

1360
02:00:24,130 --> 02:00:25,680
这现场看上去像什么
What's it look like?

1361
02:00:27,420 --> 02:00:28,470
那真相怎么办
What about the truth?

1362
02:00:28,970 --> 02:00:31,390
怎么才能抓到真到的凶手
What about getting the guys
who really did this?

1363
02:00:31,470 --> 02:00:33,470
将他们绳之以法
What about bringing him to justice?

1364
02:00:34,640 --> 02:00:36,270
我刚刚做完了
l just did.

1365
02:00:43,820 --> 02:00:46,940
怎样洗清巴尔的罪名
What about clearing Barr?
What about clearing you?

1366
02:00:47,150 --> 02:00:48,790
洗清你的罪名
l have faith you'll sort it out.

1367
02:00:48,820 --> 02:00:50,660
你会解决的 我听说你当上了检察官
And l hear you have an in
with the local D.A.

1368
02:00:50,780 --> 02:00:53,000
这期间你会干什么去
But what happens to you
in the meantime?

1369
02:00:53,160 --> 02:00:55,000
和以前一样 继续流浪
l keep moving. Same as always.

1370
02:00:55,120 --> 02:00:57,290
等等 那是我的汽车吗
Wait, is that my car?

1371
02:01:04,250 --> 02:01:05,300
这位女士
This the lady?

1372
02:01:06,170 --> 02:01:08,340
海伦-罗丁,马丁-凯时
Helen Rodin, Martin Cash.

1373
02:01:08,670 --> 02:01:09,800
幸会
A pleasure.

1374
02:01:11,180 --> 02:01:13,350
你看起来糟透了 大兵
You look like hell there, Army.

1375
02:01:13,470 --> 02:01:17,150
你问我是不是害怕象巴尔那样的结果
You asked if l was afraid
l'd end up like Barr. l'm not.

1376
02:01:17,350 --> 02:01:19,190
我不怕 我恐怕最终会像这家伙一样
l'm afraid l'll end up like this guy.

1377
02:01:19,310 --> 02:01:22,110
这里有好几具尸体 咱们走吧
There's a lot of dead bodies out here.
So let's get to it.

1378
02:01:22,190 --> 02:01:25,030
- 我们该去哪儿呢
- 等等 这就完了
-We should probably go.
-Wait. That's it?

1379
02:01:25,520 --> 02:01:26,700
结束了吗
lt's just over?

1380
02:01:27,820 --> 02:01:29,540
你会没事的 大律师
You'll be all right, counsellor.

1381
02:01:29,690 --> 02:01:32,370
不 我需要你的时候怎么办
No. What if l need you?
How will l find you?

1382
02:01:32,660 --> 02:01:33,870
你不需要我了
You don't need me.

1383
02:01:35,490 --> 02:01:36,790
不需要了
Not any more.

1384
02:01:39,370 --> 02:01:40,710
记下她的电话号友 我们走
Get her number. Let's go!

1385
02:01:57,220 --> 02:01:59,220
我是海伦-罗丁 你的律师
l'm Helen Rodin, your attorney.

1386
02:02:00,230 --> 02:02:03,980
本次谈话受律师诉讼委托人权益保护
This conversation is protected
by attorney-client privilege.

1387
02:02:04,060 --> 02:02:05,060
你明白这什么意思吗
You understand what that means?

1388
02:02:05,190 --> 02:02:06,240
是的
Yeah.

1389
02:02:06,310 --> 02:02:08,570
警察没找你谈过话 对吗
Now, the police didn't
talk to you, did they?

1390
02:02:08,730 --> 02:02:10,580
没有我在场 他们不能和你谈话
They're not allowed
to do that without me here.

1391
02:02:14,570 --> 02:02:16,250
情况多严重
How bad was it?

1392
02:02:18,240 --> 02:02:19,590
有多少人
How many did l...

1393
02:02:20,750 --> 02:02:22,750
你不记得那件事了
You don't remember
anything about the incident?

1394
02:02:26,380 --> 02:02:27,420
不记得
No.

1395
02:02:28,920 --> 02:02:32,090
我听到护士和警察在外面的谈话
But l could hear the nurses
talking to those cops out there.

1396
02:02:36,260 --> 02:02:38,430
我不记得自己为什么要杀人
l don't even remember wanting to do it!

1397
02:02:43,940 --> 02:02:45,280
这一点我不抗辩
Look, l'm not gonna fight this.

1398
02:02:46,770 --> 02:02:49,120
如果他们说是我干的 那我就干了
lf they say l done it, then l did.

1399
02:02:49,770 --> 02:02:51,450
以前我也干过这事
l done things before.

1400
02:02:54,110 --> 02:02:55,460
我做了坏事
l did something bad.

1401
02:02:58,120 --> 02:02:59,290
很坏
Real bad.

1402
02:03:03,120 --> 02:03:04,790
很久以前
A long time ago.

1403
02:03:08,290 --> 02:03:09,970
我逃脱了罪名
And l got away with it.

1404
02:03:17,640 --> 02:03:18,810
詹姆斯
James,

1405
02:03:19,140 --> 02:03:20,980
这地方你熟吗
how well do you know this place?

1406
02:03:32,280 --> 02:03:33,650
很熟悉
Pretty well.

1407
02:03:34,320 --> 02:03:36,040
要是你做 你会怎么做
And how do you think
you would have done it?

1408
02:03:39,490 --> 02:03:40,830
我猜
l guess

1409
02:03:46,830 --> 02:03:48,830
我会把车停在调整公路上
l would have parked up on the highway.

1410
02:03:49,290 --> 02:03:51,840
让太阳照在我背上
The sun would be at my back
that time of day.

1411
02:03:53,500 --> 02:03:54,630
我有面包车
l got a van.

1412
02:03:55,970 --> 02:03:57,640
枪架在车后部
Set up in back.

1413
02:03:58,340 --> 02:04:00,690
用不着担心弹壳会飞出去
Wouldn't have to worry about my brass.

1414
02:04:02,510 --> 02:04:04,520
不留痕迹你 说我这么做对吗
Get away real clean, too.

1415
02:04:08,024 --> 02:04:10,026
That sound about right?

1416
02:04:11,520 --> 02:04:13,700
听上去你是行家
Sounds as if you know your stuff.

1417
02:04:18,660 --> 02:04:20,030
我忘记你的名字
l forget your name.

1418
02:04:20,700 --> 02:04:22,040
海伦
lt's Helen.

1419
02:04:23,700 --> 02:04:25,040
海伦-罗丁
Helen Rodin.

1420
02:04:30,670 --> 02:04:32,840
你会没事的 詹姆斯
You're going to be okay, James.

1421
02:04:34,000 --> 02:04:35,720
我会保护你
l am gonna take care of you.

1422
02:04:35,880 --> 02:04:37,380
你不能保护我
You can't protect me.

1423
02:04:40,680 --> 02:04:42,020
没有人能 有人要害我
No one can.

1424
02:04:42,220 --> 02:04:43,560
什么
From what?

1425
02:04:45,010 --> 02:04:46,060
谁
From who?

1426
02:04:47,560 --> 02:04:49,230
有个人
There's this guy.

1427
02:04:52,900 --> 02:04:54,400
他好像是警官
He's a kind of cop.

1428
02:04:56,360 --> 02:04:58,030
至少他过去是
At least he used to be.

1429
02:04:59,240 --> 02:05:01,240
他不在乎法律
He doesn't care about the law.

1430
02:05:02,910 --> 02:05:04,910
不在乎证据
He doesn't care about proof.

1431
02:05:06,040 --> 02:05:07,750
只在乎什么是公正
He only cares about what's right.

1432
02:05:08,084 --> 02:05:09,919
Look at me when l'm talking to you!

1433
02:05:10,250 --> 02:05:11,750
他知道我做什么
He knows what l did.

1434
02:05:13,710 --> 02:05:14,760
他知道我在哪里
He knows where l am.

1435
02:05:16,380 --> 02:05:19,260
他向我承诺过
And this guy, he made me a promise.

1436
02:05:19,550 --> 02:05:20,600
如果我再遇到麻烦
l said, shut your mouth!

1437
02:05:21,764 --> 02:05:23,933
lf l ever got in trouble again,

1438
02:05:25,600 --> 02:05:26,940
他会来救我
he'd be there.
